Adquiri em Julho/2018, um telefone top de linha, Galaxy S9 plus por R$ 4.000,00 (quatro mil reais) na intenção de permanecer com o aparelho por pelo menos uns 3 anos, contudo, logo após o término da garantia, Dezembro/2019 o aparelho começou a apresentar defeito na tela, *simplesmente apaga*, momento em que começa a superaquecer. De se observar que o aparelho não sofreu qualquer acidente, foi submetido a usos desgastante, poeira, água ou algo que o valha, estando a carcaça perfeita, em razão dos cuidados e capas de proteção adquiridas. Muito embora seja uma marca top de linha, com preços exorbitantes, é inadmissível a aquisição de um bem durável que não chega a durar um ano e meio. A assistência técnica sem garantia orçou em R$ 2.200,00 a manutenção, não tendo qualquer suporte do fabricante. Decepcionado com a SAMSUNG. Não recomendo a aquisição dos aparelhos ditos tops de linha, pois a duração não é nem de longe a desejada. Em matemática simples, R$ 4.000,00 : 17 meses = R$ 235,30 por mês para usar o aparelho. . Aguardo posicionamento da fabricante para eventual mudança de entendimento quanto ao pós venda e durabilidade do aparelho top de linha.

) Dr. Torsten Trey, Executive Director of the NGO Doctors Against Forced Organ Harvesting (DAFOH), received the prestigious 2019 Mother Teresa Memorial Award for Social Justice at an event hosted by the Harmony Foundation at Taj Land’s End, Mumbai, on November 3, 2019.


Winners of the Mother Teresa Memorial Award (Photo courtesy Mark Luburic)

The program was well attended by other prominent award winners, Consuls General, CEOs, and celebrities. The award recognized over a decade of work to create awareness of the Chinese regime’s forced organ harvesting from Falun Gong practitioners and other prisoners of conscience.


Dr. Torsten Trey accepting the award (Photo courtesy Mark Luburic)

The Harmony Foundation acknowledged DAFOH’s nomination for the Nobel Peace Prize in 2016 and its continuing efforts to focus on unethical organ harvesting practices. “Noteworthy and admirable” was DAFOH’s ability to initiate a petition calling for an end to China’s forced organ harvesting and present it to the United Nations High Commission for Human Rights, the foundation said. The petition garnered more than two million signatures worldwide within three years.

What am I supposed to do while driving? wear illegal bluetooth earbuds?!? The last 3 years have been one bad decision after another. Dropping the Active line(last was S8), preventing glass screen protectors (S10), now no headphones.
Seriously you have three models: instead of base, plus, and ultra they should have Base, Audio, Visual. The base could be the same as the S20. The Audio only has a 2 or 3 camera setup and in the place includes a headphone jack perhaps with improved output levels, the Visual has the bigger screen and eleventy bazillion cameras so hipsters can flex their e-peen.

Also who cares about the "stunning lines" of their fragile phone? they all look the same in that plastic case you're forced to shove it in... In the last 5 years I've been using "Active" phones with no case and only a tempered glass screen protector. Guess what; it's thinner than the standard S line when they're in even the smallest of cases and I've never damaged the phone. Sure the add-on tempered glass protector has cracked a couple times but it's removable and for free lifetime replacements the phone looks new again.

For the record I've had a Galaxy S3, S6Active, S8Active.

Where is the focus on audio?

I know you want to sell disposable highly profitable Galaxy Buds, but come on now.

Why not challenge and beat LG's Quad dac and amp that comes alive with power hungry headphones, while still keeping the latest Hidef Bluetooth codecs for audio, LDAC, APTXHD, and add MQA decoding.

Not to mention better stereo recording with a standard app that allows layered recording at 24 bits, with editing features.
I understand the focus on video and photos, 8K, 4K, slo-mo, live mode, night mode.

And I appreciate the 128GB base (sorry apple), and ability to add more by sd cards (sorry apple), which you will need if you do a lot of video and photos.

But come on now..

120hz OLED color accurate, 6000 mah battery, 2 usb ports, and a headphone jack and class leading speakers are available in a ROG 2 phone for $589. with no hole, curve or notch in the display (which is a defective display)
I was really hoping, you used Lenovo's reverse notch (hood-crown), to give us a flat screen with no interruptions to the content on the display, like your tv's's monitors, and l;laptops.

And better stereo speakers, and a pro level dac and amp and 3.5 mm headphone jack, along with a 2.5 mm balanced jack on the ultra, and 2 sd cards, for backup, or extended recording.

Do not get me wrong, I am impressed with the tech, build quality, camera features, 865 chip, 5G, color options.

But like I , myself and other have said, you and almost every phone company ditches the headphone jack, not for thinness, not for water resistance, but just like Apple, to gain new revenue strings, once you introduce your own branded, disposable, $10 to make, $100-$250 to buy ear buds, and easy to lose dongles that are often rebought, and were never needed before.

This shows complete disrespect, to loyal Samsung users, who agreed with you trolling of apple's removal of the headphone jack, and we thought you cared about all of us equally wired or unwired, and you have one of the best headphone/hearing calibration apps.

I was truly hoping you would surpass LG in headphone audio, wired and wireless, and stereo recording, and the rumored Sony Walkman branded phones.
But no.

So I will stand by my commitment, as others will never to buy a smartphone without a good quality headphone jack standard, whether that be LG, Apple, Samsung, Google, One Plus, or whoever.
